MultiPixel Ecosystem Overview
Relimintor (Raptor4 / MultiPixel)

1. INTRODUCTION
The MultiPixel ecosystem includes:
• the game
• mods
• servers
• monetization systems
• community governance
• safety systems

2. MODS
• Mods are allowed for personal use.
• Mods are owned by MultiPixel.
• Mods require approval to be shared or monetized.

3. SERVERS
• Servers may operate without approval if non-commercial and non-political.
• Servers require approval for monetization or restricted topics.
• MultiPixel receives 30% of gross revenue.

4. POLITICAL SERVERS
• Require explicit approval.
• Must follow strict rules.
• Must be clearly labeled.

5. MONETIZATION
• Mods: 15% revenue share.
• Servers: 30% revenue share.
• Only lootboxes, currency, and cosmetic roles allowed.

6. SAFETY
• Anti-cheat enforced.
• No harassment or illegal content.
• Servers must moderate.

7. BRANDING
• Use of MultiPixel branding requires approval.
• Unofficial servers/mods must be labeled.

8. DATA
• MultiPixel collects server join logs, chat logs, and usage data.
• Servers may collect join/leave logs and chat logs.

9. ENFORCEMENT
MultiPixel may:
• revoke approvals
• ban servers
• remove mods
• issue DMCA takedowns
• impose fines
• pursue legal action
